        <tr>
            <td bgcolor="#4866a1"><font face="verdana" color=#D7D3DE size=2>Congratulations! &nbsp;I would love to see your sons face Christmas morning! &nbsp;I'm a real believer in pound puppies. &nbsp;The healthiest, happiest and 'highest personality' dogs I've ever had have been mixed breed. &nbsp;Most people at shelters are very willling to fit you with the perfect puppy. &nbsp;You can start looking now and let them know what kind of dog you're looking for and they'll keep an eye out for you. &nbsp;&quot;Furburbia' in Cottonwood mall is a great place t start. &nbsp;It doesn't have the 'institutional feel of shelters. &nbsp;Petsmart adoption days are great too. &nbsp;These are usually dogs who are being 'fostered' until they find a permanent home. &nbsp;They tend to be a bit more 'mannered' than dogs who've been cooped up in a cage. &nbsp;But even the one's who haven't been fostered coe along nicely with time. &nbsp;Don't forget to send your son and puppy to puppy school, they'll both love it! &nbsp;Have an awesome Christmas!!! &nbsp; &nbsp;Robin
</td>
        </tr>
